SKBGROS.SKBGROS_LONG_DESC:
The African/African-American Studies Program (AFA) at Ellucian University offers students the opportunity to engage with the histories, stories, and experiences of Africans and peoples of African descent around the world. These often-overlooked narratives can help us makes sense of a globalized world, present-day socio-political issues in the US, and our own identities.
The program currently offers a minor or certificate to Ellucian students. Our faculty members are drawn from diverse academic fields and backgrounds, and offer a wide range of classes . We are committed to encouraging student research and community involvement beyond the classroom.
